<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PersonNote/2424> rdfs:label "Person Note: #2424" ;
	a dprr:PersonNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The authors at three different periods of the three Porcian laws cannot be identified with certainty, nor did they with certainty hold the tribunate of the Plebs. All three regulated corporal punishment and the right of appeal of Roman citizens (Cic. Rep. 2.54). The first may perhaps be attributed to Cato the Censor (see Fest. 266 L; FOR 1.182-184), a second to a Porcius Laeca (Grueber, CRRBM 1.151), and a third of uncertain attribution forbade scourging a Roman in the city (Sall. Cat. 51.21; see Grueber CRRBM 2.301). One Porcian law permitted condemned persons to go into exile (Sall. Cat. 51.40). See Niccolini, FTP 424-426; Botsford, Roman Assemblies 250-253." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PersonNote/1734> rdfs:label "Person Note: #1734" ;
	a dprr:PersonNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/28> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/14> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Censorius." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PersonNote/1733> rdfs:label "Person Note: #1733" ;
	a dprr:PersonNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/28> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/13> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Interesse an Augural- und Pontifikalrecht konnte offensichtlich auch ein Nichtpriester haben. Die Schrift de agricultura zeigt den privaten und bäuerlichen Hintergrund eines reichen Interesses an Religion." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PersonNote/1732> rdfs:label "Person Note: #1732" ;
	a dprr:PersonNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/28> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/12> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Szemler 1972:144, Kienast 1954:41 (je zum Augurat, ablehnend); Bauman 1983:160-170 (zustimmend)." .
